[1] Hong Kong (imported)
Date: Sat 11 Aug 2007
Source: Health and Community News.gov.hk [edited]
<http://www.news.gov.hk/en/category/healthandcommunity/070811/html/070811en05008.htm>

The Centre for Health Protection has confirmed 2 dengue fever cases,
one imported and the other under investigation.
A 21-year-old Tseung Kwan O man came down with fever, muscle pain and
tiredness on 30 Jul [2007] and was admitted to Princess Margaret
Hospital 4 Aug [2007]. He was discharged 8 Aug [2007]. He travelled
to Indonesia with 9 people 6 July- 4 Aug [2007]. His family members
and travel companions have no symptoms.
The 2nd case involved a 57-year-old Tuen Mun man. He came down with
fever, headache and a skin rash on 31 July [2007]. He was sent to
Tuen Mun Hospital 4 Aug [2007] and was discharged 9 Aug [2007]. He
visited Macau 23 Jul - 1 Aug [2007] The centre is investigating the
source of infection and has notified the Macau health authority. His
family members have no symptoms.
Prior to these 2 new cases, 19 imported cases had been reported this
year. Last year [2006] saw 31 cases.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED rapporteur Brent Barrett
[These 2 cases are probably imported from Indonesia and Macau. There
is no indication that they were acquired in Hong Kong. Without
knowing the status of vector mosquitoes in Hong Kong, it is not
possible to predict the risk of dengue virus transmission there.
An interactive map of Hong Kong can be accessed at:
<http://www.lonelyplanet.com/mapshells/north_east_asia/hong_kong/hong_kong.htm>
- Mod.TY]
