[6] Brazil (Caera)
Date: Sat 04 Aug 2007
Fonte: Diario do Nordeste [in Portuguese, trans. and summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://diariodonordeste.globo.com/materia.asp?codigo=458330>

Of the 178 DHF cases this year [2007], 7 have died. In 2006 there
were 15 deaths.
-------------------------------------------
The numbers of confirmed dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) cases in
Caera this year [2007] now have passed the numbers registered in
2006. By just the middle of this year, the numbers of people infected
with the hemorrhagic type of the disease reached 178, compared to 172
in the entire past year [2006], according to the Epidemiological
Bulletin issued yesterday [3 Aug 2007] by the Secretary of Health of
the state of Ceara.
The greatest number of cases have occurred in Fortaleza, with 91
proved positives, followed by the city of Crato with 17, and Brejo
Santo with 13, There are an additional 65 cases under investigation,
according to the Secretary of Health.
In relation to the total numbers of cases of the disease [dengue], in
one week there were 695 people infected. There are, as of now, 17
231 [dengue] cases in 160 municipalities [in the state in 2007].
Forteleza has registered the greatest number with 6822 occurrences of
the disease, equivalent to 39.95 per cent of the total in Ceara state.
Almost 7000 [dengue] cases have been confirmed in Forteleza, the
greatest number registered in 10-19 years.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>
